data.description: COME AND SEE!!! Newly renovated home in walking distance to Elementary and Middle School!! 5 bedroom , 3 bath home with unique layout not typically seen in KC area . New paint inside and outside , flooring , countertops , appliances , fixtures , vanities , ALL NEW . As you walk in , you first encounter the front room with LVP flooring , perfect to sit and enjoy coffee under natural light. The kitchen is equipped with new quartz countertops , oven and microwave , as well as a mini fridge perfect for kids .The dining area is enough for an oversized table , also finished with lvp. The oversized family /great room is one of the highlights of the home . More than enough space to host as many people as you would like , with a fireplace and built in shelves perfectly complimenting the space.Going out the sliding patio door, you walk out on the recently painted deck leading to the sizable flat backyard equipped with a shed . Upstairs you will find the hallway bath and two bedrooms , as well as the master bedroom and bath . The spacious hallway full bath has a new vanity and toilet , accented by the newly tiled floor and shower . Down the hall is two bedrooms with sitting bay window seats that open for deep storage with new can lights and carpet . Then you have the Master Suite , fit for comfort with space for seating as well as a screened porch attached that oversees the backyard and perfect for relaxing outdoors . Walk in closet,his and hers vanities , and a deep soaker tub to enjoy ! It can't be said enough, EVERYTHING IS NEW. In the lower level  you find two more bedrooms , one with a fireplace , a bathroom with a shower as well as the laundry area . The basement offers plenty of space for storage , and did I mention the New Furnace and Water Heater ?? Outside , enjoy your oversized driveway perfect for basketball! Pleasant Lea Park is also a few Steps  away !!! This beautiful park has walking trails , Pickleball, basketball, picnic area ,and a playground !IT WON'T LAST!
